---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Starting with CO in Scrabble"
  description="Best CO- words for Scrabble scoring. CO is an extremely productive prefix with many valid short words. Free Scrabble guide. Free word finder included."
  keywords="co words scrabble, words starting with co, co prefix scrabble, combine scrabble, compose scrabble, scrabble co words list, two letter prefix scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Starting with CO in Scrabble",
    "description": "Best CO- words for Scrabble scoring with strategy for using this productive two-letter prefix.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-20",
    "dateModified": "2026-07-06",
    "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Raj Naik", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/about/" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-starting-with-co" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many words starting with CO are valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are over 1,200 valid CO- words across TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, making CO one of the three most productive two-letter prefixes in Scrabble (alongside DE and RE). Words range from 3 letters (COB, COD, COG) to 15+ letters. The prefix covers everything from COB (3 letters, 7pts) to COMMUNICATION (13 letters)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best CO words for scoring in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The highest-scoring common CO words include COZY (18 points), COXCOMB (20 points), and COMPLEX (20 points). For practical gameplay, 7-letter CO bingos like COMPUTE (13+50), COMPLEX (20+50), and CONVOKE (16+50) are the best targets because they combine high base scores with the 50-point bingo bonus." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can CO be played as a word by itself in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "CO is NOT valid as a standalone word in either TWL or SOWPODS. The shortest valid CO words are 3 letters: COB (7pts), COD (6pts), COG (6pts), COL (5pts), CON (5pts), COO (5pts), COP (7pts), COR (5pts), COS (5pts), COT (5pts), COW (8pts), COX (12pts), COY (8pts), COZ (14pts). These 3-letter words are extremely useful for tight plays." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-4 pb-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Words Starting With Co" />

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Starting with CO in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-20">June 20, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        CO ranks among the top three most productive two-letter prefixes in Scrabble, alongside DE and RE. With over 1,200 valid words, CO- combinations appear in nearly every game — from short power plays like COX (12pts) and COZ (14pts) to devastating bingo words like COMPUTE and COMPLEX. This guide covers the best CO words for competitive scoring, focusing on short high-value plays and bingo-length opportunities.
      </p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1,200+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid CO Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Score (7-letter)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3–15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Range</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card Grid: Most Useful CO Words -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 Best for Bingos</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COMPUTE (7) · COMPLEX (7) · CONFORM (7) · CONVERT (7) · COMPOSE (7)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚡ Highest Scoring</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COXCOMB (20) · COZY (18) · COMPLEX (20) · CONJUX (22) · CONVEX (18)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📝 Most Common</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COMBINE · COMMAND · COMPANY · COMPARE · COMPLETE · CONFIRM · CONNECT · CONTAIN</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Easy to Build</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COB · COD · COG · CON · COP · COT · COW · COX · COY · COZ · COAT · CODE · COIN · COLD</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">CO Words by Length (3–5 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Short CO words are absolute workhorses in Scrabble. The 3-letter CO words are especially valuable — they fit anywhere on the board and many contain high-scoring letters like X, Z, and W. Memorize these for tight positions and parallel plays.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">3 Letters (Power Plays)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COX (12) · COZ (14) · COW (8) · COY (8) · COB (7) · COP (7) · COD (6) · COG (6) · CON (5) · COT (5) · COO (5)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">4–5 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COZY (18) · COPY (11) · COAX (13) · COOK (10) · COLD (7) · COME (8) · CORD (7) · CORE (6) · CORK (10) · CORN (6) · COVER (10) · COXED (15)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">CO has <span class="text-white font-medium">14 valid 3-letter words</span> — more than almost any other two-letter start. This makes it invaluable for tight board positions where only 3 letters fit. COX (12pts) and COZ (14pts) are among the highest-scoring 3-letter words in the entire game.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">CO Words (6 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Six-letter CO words bridge the gap between short plays and bingos. They score well on their own and can be extended with S plurals or other suffixes to reach bingo length on your next turn.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">6 Letters (Best Picks)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CONVEX (18) · COMBAT (12) · COMPLY (15) · CONVEY (14) · COPIED (11) · CORNER (8) · COSTLY (11) · COUPLE (10) · COWARD (12) · COYOTE (11)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo-Length CO Words (7 Letters)</h2>

      <p>Seven-letter CO bingos are highly accessible because the prefix only uses 2 tiles. You have 5 full tiles for the root word — and with CO being so productive, the chances of landing a bingo are excellent when you hold C and O together.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7-Letter Bingos (High Value)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COMPLEX (20+50) · COMPUTE (13+50) · CONVOKE (16+50) · COWBOYS (17+50) · COMPACT (15+50)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7-Letter Bingos (Common)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COMMAND (14+50) · COMBINE (13+50) · COMMENT (13+50) · COMPANY (16+50) · COMPARE (13+50) · COMPOSE (13+50) · CONCERT (11+50) · CONFIRM (14+50) · CONNECT (11+50) · CONSENT (9+50) · CONTACT (11+50) · CONTAIN (9+50) · CONTENT (9+50) · CONTROL (9+50) · CONVERT (12+50) · CORRECT (11+50) · COUNCIL (11+50) · COUNTRY (12+50) · COURAGE (10+50)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">CO Words (8+ Letters)</h2>

      <p>Eight-letter and longer CO words are mostly played as extensions of existing board words. Adding CO before OPERATE makes COOPERATE. These extension opportunities are nearly endless with such a productive prefix.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">8–9 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COEXISTS · COINCIDE · COLLAPSE · COLORFUL · COMBINED · COMEBACK · COMMENCE · COMMERCE · COMMUNAL · COMPETED · COMPOSED · COMPUTED · CONCRETE · CONFINED · CONFLICT · CONFUSED · CONGRESS · CONJURED · CONQUEST · COOKBOOK</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">10+ Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">COMBUSTION · COMMENTARY · COMMITMENT · COMPANIONS · COMPARISON · COMPELLING · COMPENSATE · COMPETITOR · COMPLEXITY · COMPREHEND · COMPROMISE · CONFESSION · CONFIDENCE · CONFRONTED · CONTROLLED · CONVENIENT · CONVERSION · CONVICTION · COORDINATE</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Short CO Words for Premium Squares</h2>

      <p>CO's real power lies in its short, high-scoring words. Unlike UNDER or TRANS which need long plays to shine, CO dominates in tight board positions where 3–5 letter words hit premium squares perfectly.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">COX and COZ on premium squares:</span> COX (12pts) on a Triple Letter X = 30pts for 3 tiles. COZ (14pts) on a Double Word = 28pts. These tiny words punch far above their weight when positioned correctly. Always check if CO+premium letter can reach a bonus square.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">COZY is a stealth weapon:</span> At 18 points base, COZY is one of the highest-scoring 4-letter words in Scrabble. On a DW square it scores 36; on TW it hits 54. The Z on a TL within COZY gives you exceptional value for just 4 tiles placed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play with CO- words:</span> Play a 3-letter CO word parallel to an existing word, forming multiple 2-letter cross-words. CON next to an existing word can form 3 cross-words simultaneously — each one scoring independently. This multiplies your total score dramatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Set up bingo extensions:</span> Play COMP, CONV, or CONF as 4-letter plays now — then extend to COMPUTE, CONVERT, or CONFIRM on your next turn for the bingo bonus. Your opponent often cannot block a front-extension because they do not know which word you are building toward.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">CO vs DE: Which Prefix Wins?</h2>

      <p>Both CO and DE are two-letter prefixes with enormous word counts. Here is how they stack up for competitive play.</p>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ CO Advantages</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">More high-scoring 3-letter words (COX, COZ, COW, COY). Better access to X and Z tiles. 14 valid 3-letter words. COZY is one of the best 4-letter plays in the game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ CO Drawbacks</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CO is not valid standalone (DE is in SOWPODS). C tile is worth 3pts but appears less frequently (2 per bag). Fewer front-hook opportunities than DE. Requires C which is a medium-frequency tile.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Dictionary Note</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">CO is <span class="text-white font-medium">not valid as a standalone word</span> in either TWL or SOWPODS. The minimum play is 3 letters (COB, COD, COG, etc.). However, CO- appears as a hyphenated prefix in many dictionaries — only the unhyphenated compound forms are valid in Scrabble.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-cheat-sheet/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
